atesBindingFromClosureCapturingNestedPropertyPath() {\\n        PersonModel person = new PersonModel(new AddressModel('Paris'))\\n        ClosureTriggerBinding triggerBinding = new ClosureTriggerBinding(Collections.emptyMap())\\n        triggerBinding.setClosure({ person.address.city })\\n        RecordingTargetBinding targetBinding = new RecordingTargetBinding()\\n\\n        FullBinding fullBinding = triggerBinding.createBinding(triggerBinding, targetBinding)\\n\\n        try {\\n            fullBinding.bind()\\n            fullBinding.update()\\n\\n            assertThat(targetBinding.values).containsExactly('Paris')\\n\\n            person.getAddress().setCity('Prague')\\n            fullBinding.update()\\n\\n            assertThat(targetBinding.values.first()).isEqualTo('Paris')\\n            assertThat(targetBinding.values.last()).isEqualTo('Prague')\\n        } finally {\\n            fullBinding.unbind()\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class RecordingTargetBinding implements TargetBinding {\\n        private final List<Object> values = new ArrayList<>()\\n\\n        @Override\\n        void updateTargetValue(Object value) {\\n            values.add(value)\\n        }\\n\\n        List<Object> getValues() {\\n            return values\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class PersonModel {\\n        private final PropertyChangeSupport propertyChangeSupport = new PropertyChangeSupport(this)\\n        private AddressModel address\\n\\n        private PersonModel(AddressModel address) {\\n            this.address = address\\n        }\\n\\n        AddressModel getAddress() {\\n            return address\\n        }\\n\\n        void setAddress(AddressModel address) {\\n            AddressModel oldAddress = this.address\\n            this.address = address\\n            propertyChangeSupport.firePropertyChange('address', oldAddress, address)\\n        }\\n\\n        void addPropertyChangeListener(String propertyName, PropertyChangeListener listener) {\\n            propertyChangeSupport.addPropertyChangeListener(propertyName, listener)\\n        }\\n\\n        void removePropertyChangeListener(String propertyName, PropertyChangeListener listener) {\\n            propertyChangeSupport.removePropertyChangeListener(propertyName, listener)\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class AddressModel {\\n        private final PropertyChangeSupport propertyChangeSupport = new PropertyChangeSupport(this)\\n        private String city\\n\\n        private AddressModel(String city) {\\n            this.city = city\\n        }\\n\\n        String getCity() {\\n            return city\\n        }\\n\\n        void setCity(String city) {\\n            String oldCity = this.city\\n            this.city = city\\n            propertyChangeSupport.firePropertyChange('city', oldCity, city)\\n        }\\n\\n        void addPropertyChangeListener(String propertyName, PropertyChangeListener listener) {\\n            propertyChangeSupport.addPropertyChangeListener(propertyName, listener)\\n        }\\n\\n        void removePropertyChangeListener(String propertyName, PropertyChangeListener listener) {\\n            propertyChangeSupport.removePropertyChangeListener(propertyName, listener)\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778372400818}, {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_C2xpetnAF61qLfpaTwMajO5f|fc_0ac9a0cf1660ca530169ffcf309e6081a2b7bb929f3d389d3d\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_groovy.groovy_swing\\n\\nimport groovy.beans.PropertyAccessor\\nimport org.apache.groovy.swing.binding.PropertyBinding\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assert