ext.\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:18:  - `compute_class_delta(...)`: compares previous/current report for one class and computes newly covered vs still-uncovered call sites.\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:19:  - `format_call_sites(...)`: converts uncovered/newly-covered call-site lists into prompt-ready bullet text.\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:63:                Strategy->>Agent: Render class-targeted prompt with uncovered call sites\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:75:                Report-->>Strategy: Newly covered and still-uncovered call sites\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:79:                else Class still has uncovered call sites\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:80:                    Note over Strategy,Report: Retry the same class with updated uncovered call sites.\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:4:> [Dynamic-access strategy](dynamic-access-strategy.md)\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:39:        DAReport[(\\\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\\\")]\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:164:- **Required prompts**: `dynamic-access-iteration`.\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:167:- **Loop**: parses `dynamic-access-coverage.json`; iterates over classes with\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:168:  uncovered call sites. For each class it renders the iteration prompt with\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:169:  uncovered call-site lists and the coverage delta, runs the inner test loop,\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:182:- **Required prompts**: `optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration`.\\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:185:  uncovered call sites) in a single prompt, then runs the inner test loop. On\\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:48:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:63:| Output directory | Call